This week, April 11-17, 2021 marks the fourth annual Black Maternal Health Week, created and led by the Black Mamas Matter Alliance.

This is a week of building awareness, deepening the conversation, and educating ourselves about the structural racism in our society and healthcare system. Structural inequities lead to disparities in maternal health, including elevated rates of maternal mortality in Black people. 

We at PPG are committed to providing comprehensive care to all patients, confronting our own biases, and ending racial disparities in maternal and child health outcomes. As allies, we commit to actively practicing anti-racism and continuing to educate ourselves about the structural racism in our society and the healthcare system. 

